def clean_column(col):
    return col.strip().lower().replace(' ', '_').replace('-', '_')
```

In this function, `str.strip()` removes leading and trailing whitespaces from the string. Then, `str.lower()` converts all characters in the string to lowercase. `str.replace(' ', '_')` replaces all spaces with underscores. Lastly, `str.replace('-', '_')` replaces any hyphens with underscores.
